# 31_inspector_sections_smoke — exercises s222 m2's `inspector`
# Scriptable. Two verbs, no queries — the test is visual: the
# operator runs the script and watches the right-panel sections
# collapse and re-open one at a time.
#
# ── What this Scriptable is for ──────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Scott's demo-prep workflow: before running a script that mutates
# (say) the styles library, the inspector should be set up so the
# user can SEE the changes happen. That means collapsing every
# right-panel section except the one the demo is about to use.
# Without these verbs the operator does the collapse-and-open by
# hand before each demo run; with them it's a two-line preamble in
# the script itself.
#
# ── Verb surface ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   inspector collapse_all       — close every right-panel section AND
#                                  every PropertiesPanel-internal
#                                  collapsible. Spans BOTH registries
#                                  via MainWindow's existing
#                                  collapse_all_inspector_sections
#                                  (originally built for the s202 m6
#                                  keyboard quick-jump float).
#   inspector open "<title>"     — open one named section. Limited to
#                                  right-panel sections today (those
#                                  registered in MainWindow's
#                                  m_sec_apply: Layers, Library,
#                                  Swatches, Styles, Themes, Documents,
#                                  Preview, plus the Content group).
#                                  PropertiesPanel-internal sections
#                                  aren't reached by this verb yet —
#                                  the cascade path lives inside
#                                  MainWindow::focus_inspector_on and
#                                  hasn't been lifted out yet.
#
# ── Test isolation ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This smoke MUTATES inspector view-state across the run (it
# collapses everything and opens a sequence of sections). The state
# is persisted — when the script finishes, the right-panel sections
# will be in whatever state the last `open` left them. That's
# acceptable for an inspector-prep verb; the next session's
# load-project will restore the saved state if needed, and the
# user can collapse-all by hand from the keyboard (Ctrl+Backtick or
# whatever the current binding is).
#
# No `count_before`-style baseline capture; there's nothing to
# round-trip. The visual confirmation IS the test.

#[sub] Registry sanity — `inspector` should be visible in `list`.
#[sub] (Same Scriptable-registry plumbing as styles/swatches/layers/
#[sub] guides; the registry entry is created in InspectorScriptable's
#[sub] base-class ctor.)
list

#[sub] Phase 1: collapse everything. After this line, every right-
#[sub] panel section AND every PropertiesPanel-internal collapsible
#[sub] should be closed. The arrow glyphs should all show ▸, no
#[sub] section bodies visible. The persisted state (project's
#[sub] sec_*_open fields) is also updated — schedule_save fires.

inspector collapse_all

#[sub] Phase 2: open one section. The Styles section should now be
#[sub] visible — the dropdown for category selection and the chip
#[sub] grid for the active category. Other sections stay collapsed.

inspector open "Styles"

#[sub] Open another. Both Styles AND Swatches should now be open;
#[sub] this verb doesn't collapse siblings (use collapse_all + open
#[sub] for that "spotlight" behaviour).

inspector open "Swatches"

#[sub] Open Layers too. Three sections open now (Styles, Swatches,
#[sub] Layers); everything else still collapsed.

inspector open "Layers"

#[sub] Unknown section title — silent no-op. apply_section_open's
#[sub] map lookup misses, returns without doing anything; no error,
#[sub] no warning, no panel state change.

inspector open "NoSuchSection"

#[sub] Empty arg — silent no-op. The Scriptable's invoke checks
#[sub] args.empty() before calling MainWindow, so this short-
#[sub] circuits there.

inspector open ""

#[sub] Phase 3: collapse and re-open just one. This is the canonical
#[sub] demo-prep preamble — close everything, then open the one
#[sub] section the script is about to mutate. Operator should see
#[sub] all three previously-open sections close, then Styles
#[sub] re-appear.

inspector collapse_all
inspector open "Styles"

#[sub] s222 m2 smoke complete. Manual verification: the right-panel
#[sub] should have Styles open and every other section closed.
#[sub] Re-running the smoke is idempotent (collapse_all + open
#[sub] always lands in the same state).
